description.narrative: By 2016, national and community systems to support all girls and boys 0-6 years old in the targeted communities with a quality start to life, early learning and developmental readiness., which contributes to Early Childhood Development, Early Learning, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Infant And Young Child Feeding, Learning Outcomes, Maternal And Newborn Health, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By the end of 2016, in Jamaica's poorest and most volatile communities, 40 per cent of 6 year old girls and boys entering primary schools master the entrance assessment and the performance of grade 4 boys and girls on national math and literacy assessments improved by 30 per cent.
